    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-18T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-18T01:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/5–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-18T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >May 18, 1945—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1639. Today’s papers published brief item quoting Secretary’s statement<note
                        n="55" xml:id="d755fn55">Made at San Francisco, May 15, 1945, Department of
                        State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, May 20, 1945, p. 940.</note> that
                    Lend-Lease deliveries will be continued in amounts necessary for achieving quick
                    and final victory with minimum losses and that no other consideration than
                    changing military situation will dictate changes in Lend-Lease program after
                    defeat of Germany.</p>
                <p>Nothing has appeared in Under Secretary’s statement<note n="56" xml:id="d755fn56"
                        >Released May 14, <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>.</note> regarding reduction in
                    Lend-Lease program for Soviet Union.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
